<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>snipGeek | Organise yourself bro</title>
	<link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Kreon|Podkova|Crushed' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css' />
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag :all %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag :defaults %>	
  <%= javascript_include_tag "prettify.js" %>
	<%= csrf_meta_tag %>
</head>
<body onload="prettyPrint()">
	<div id="wrapper">
		<section id="sticky-bar">
			<ul>
			  <% if current_user %>
					<li id="add-snip"><a href="#">+ SNiP</a></li>
					<li>Yo <%= current_user.username %> dude</li>
					<li>|</li>
					<li>logged in <strong><%= current_user.login_count %></strong> times</li>
					<li>|</li>
					<% if current_user.login_count > 1 %>
					<li>last logged in <strong><%= current_user.last_login_at.strftime("%d/%m/%Y") %></strong></li>
					<li>|</li>
					<% end %>
					<li>you currently have <strong><%= current_user.snips.count %></strong> snips!</li>
					<%= render "snips/newsnip" %>			    
					<li id="logout" class="auth">
						<%= link_to "Logout", logout_path %>
						<%= link_to "Edit Profile", edit_user_path(:current), :class => "edit-profile" %>
			  	</li>
				<% else %>
			    <li id="login-trigger" class="auth">
						<%= link_to "Register", new_user_path, :class => "new-user" %>
			    	<%= link_to "Login", login_path, :class => "login-user" %>
			  	</li>
				<% end %>			
			</ul>
		</section>
	</div>
	<section id="snips">
		<%= yield %>		
	</section>
	<% if !current_user %>
	<div id="welcome">
		<h1><strong>Hi!</strong> Welcome to snipGeek</h1>
		<p>snipGeek is an online dashboard that allows you to create an account and help manage code snippets.</p>
		<p>
			One day I realised that every time I started a new project and had to painfully crawl through previous
			projects to find different snippets of code to do different things, wouldn't it be awesome just to have
			a dashboard of everything I need in one place? Bam. snipGeek.
		</p>
		<p>
			Feedback is always, always appreciated and encouraged. If you find this site useful, or have any issues
			please feel free to give me a shout. You can contact me via email at 
			<a href="MAILTO:j@japhex.net">j@japhex.net</a> or alternatively I'm on Twitter 
			<a href="http://www.twitter.com/japhex">@Japhex</a>...oh and <a href="http://about.me/japhex">about.me</a>
			...enjoy dudes.
		</p>
	</div>	
	<% end %>
	<section id="overlay">
	</section>
	<section id="overlay-content">
	</section>
</body>
</html>
